WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.542 --> 00:00:13.041
Hey everyone, it's Sarah. Welcome back to the Pitt vlogs.

00:00:13.042 --> 00:00:15.791
In this vlog, first year mentors Kenny and Allison

00:00:15.792 --> 00:00:18.208
are going to check out the different neighborhoods of Pittsburgh.

00:00:18.792 --> 00:00:20.666
Hey everybody, I'm Kenny, and I'm Allison,

00:00:20.667 --> 00:00:22.332
and we're first year mentors here at Pitt.

00:00:22.333 --> 00:00:24.291
And today we're going to go on a tour of all the boroughs

00:00:24.292 --> 00:00:26.624
around our campus and everywhere we go you can go for free

00:00:26.625 --> 00:00:27.582
with your Pitt ID.

00:00:27.583 --> 00:00:28.957
We're going to head to the Waterfront first.

00:00:28.958 --> 00:00:29.833
We'll see you there!

00:00:37.333 --> 00:00:38.666
Hey everybody we're at the Waterfront now,

00:00:38.667 --> 00:00:40.499
about a 20-minute bus ride from campus.

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:42.874
There's a lot of really great outdoor shopping areas

00:00:42.875 --> 00:00:45.666
like Dick's, Target, then a lot of really great clothing stores.

00:00:45.667 --> 00:00:47.416
There's a bunch of awesome places to eat, too, like

00:00:47.417 --> 00:00:48.791
Burgatory and P. F. Chang's.

00:00:48.792 --> 00:00:51.457
And then one of the best movie theatres around campus.

00:00:51.458 --> 00:00:52.667
Now off to Squirrel Hill!

00:00:54.583 --> 00:00:56.041
Hey guys, we're in Squirrel Hill,

00:00:56.042 --> 00:00:57.707
which is about a 20-minute walk from campus.

00:00:57.708 --> 00:00:59.999
There's a bunch of small businesses and restaurants located here.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.832
The closest Eat'n Park is here, which is located on the main drag

00:01:02.833 --> 00:01:03.874
that's Murray Avenue.

00:01:03.875 --> 00:01:05.832
There's also a Giant Eagle and a movie theatre

00:01:05.833 --> 00:01:06.749
on this street as well.

00:01:06.750 --> 00:01:07.875
Now off to Shadyside!

00:01:11.958 --> 00:01:14.541
Here we are in Shadyside on Walnut Street.

00:01:14.542 --> 00:01:16.749
The closest Apple store to campus is right behind us.

00:01:16.750 --> 00:01:18.541
There's also a really nice bakery down the road

00:01:18.542 --> 00:01:21.207
called Prantl's and there's also a bunch of nice,

00:01:21.208 --> 00:01:22.249
cute little shops as well.

00:01:22.250 --> 00:01:24.957
In addition to that, there's also a lot of high-end clothing stores

00:01:24.958 --> 00:01:27.291
as well as a Market District and Whole Foods.

00:01:27.292 --> 00:01:28.500
Now off to South Side!

00:01:32.708 --> 00:01:35.249
Now we're in South Side, one of the most common places to go.

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:37.624
There's a lot of really great places to shop like

00:01:37.625 --> 00:01:39.291
Urban Outfitters and American Eagle

00:01:39.292 --> 00:01:41.416
and then also really great restaurants like the Cheesecake Factory

00:01:41.417 --> 00:01:42.166
behind us.

00:01:42.167 --> 00:01:43.457
And right to our left there's a movie theatre,

00:01:43.458 --> 00:01:45.874
it's the closest one to campus and a great place to go with friends.

00:01:45.875 --> 00:01:47.708
And now we're going to go to the Strip District!

00:01:50.833 --> 00:01:52.166
Hey everybody we're at the Strip District now.

00:01:52.167 --> 00:01:54.249
It's one of the most culturally diverse areas in Pittsburgh.

00:01:54.250 --> 00:01:56.582
There's a lot of great dining and shopping options.

00:01:56.583 --> 00:01:58.916
There's also a lot of different cultural places to buy food

00:01:58.917 --> 00:02:01.124
and a ton of cheap farmer's markets to go to.

00:02:01.125 --> 00:02:02.582
It's a great place to go on the weekend with

00:02:02.583 --> 00:02:04.582
your friends just to go shopping and hang out for the day.

00:02:04.583 --> 00:02:05.917
Now we're going to go head downtown!

00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:12.832
Hi guys, we're in Market Square, which is in downtown Pittsburgh.

00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:15.707
There's a lot of great places to eat here like Nola and Oyster House.

00:02:15.708 --> 00:02:18.457
It's also a really great place to hang out and grab a bite to eat

00:02:18.458 --> 00:02:21.332
before going to the cultural district to see a show with your discounted

00:02:21.333 --> 00:02:22.332
Pitt Arts ticket.

00:02:22.333 --> 00:02:23.833
Now we're off to Mount Washington!

00:02:27.875 --> 00:02:29.582
Hey everybody we're at Mount Washington now,

00:02:29.583 --> 00:02:30.999
one of the best views in the country.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:32.374
Right below us is Station Square,

00:02:32.375 --> 00:02:35.332
where you can go eat at Joe's Crab Shack or Hard Rock Cafe.

00:02:35.333 --> 00:02:37.749
And after that meal you can come up the incline.

00:02:37.750 --> 00:02:41.124
It's free with your Pitt ID to where we're at now, Mount Washington.

00:02:41.125 --> 00:02:43.082
It's a really great place for a date as well

00:02:43.083 --> 00:02:45.041
with the beautiful views and it makes a nice walk.

00:02:45.042 --> 00:02:46.500
Now we're going to head back to Oakland.

00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:48.666
Phew, what a day!

00:02:48.667 --> 00:02:51.374
I hope everybody had a good time exploring the neighborhoods with us.

00:02:51.375 --> 00:02:53.416
And remember, there's always a new place to go and

00:02:53.417 --> 00:02:55.250
in every new place there's always a new adventure!

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:57.874
We've only scratched the surface of the neighborhoods

00:02:57.875 --> 00:02:58.582
surrounding Oakland.

00:02:58.583 --> 00:03:01.124
We hope you'll check out all that Pittsburgh has to offer.

00:03:01.125 --> 00:03:02.832
Thanks for watching the Pitt vlogs

00:03:02.833 --> 00:03:04.125
and tune in next time!

